Superpropagator in a covariantly constant field 

In this section, we evaluate the heat kernel
()
in the the case of a covariantly constant gauge superfield
satisfying eq. ().
Taken together with the Bianchi identities,
this condition implies that the Yang-Mills supermultiplet
belongs to the Cartan subalgebra of the gauge group.
For this background gauge superfield,
the heat kernel () was originally
computed by Ohrndorf using the Fock-Schwinger gauge
in superspace. Here we derive,
for the first time, this exact
