from () we can immediately derive the chiral
kernel  using the prescription ().
The result for  can be shown to agree with the
exact superpropagator computed in(see also a related work), although the final relation
in (the English translation of) contains a misprint.

In conclusion, we would like to comment on the relationship
between  and the chiral propagator used
in for a calculation in the context of
the matrix model/gauge theory correspondence.
The authors of  evaluate chiral loop diagrams
in an on-shell covariantly constant SYM background,
as specified by eqs. () and (),
which is then further simplified
by formally setting  and 
while keeping .
For such a background, in the chiral representation
 is
K_+(z,z's) = -i (4 s)^2  
e ^ i (x-x')^2 /4s   
(--i  s W)^2
 I(z,z') .
This is the heat kernel corresponding to the chiral
propagator used in.




