Technical lemma 
This appendix is devoted to a derivation of eq. ().
It is in fact sufficient to prove the following relation
&(n+1)  ^A_n  ^A_1  _A_1    _A_n  _B I(z,z')_z=z' 
= n  ^A_n  ^A_1  _A_1  _A_n-1   F_A_n B  

& + (n-1)
^A_n  T_A_n B  ^C ^A_n-1  
^A_1 
_A_1  _A_n-2    F_A_n-1  B   ,
with  a positive integer.

We start with an obvious identity
  (n &+& 1)  ^A_n  ^A_1  _( A_1    _A_n  _ B  
= ^A_n  ^A_1  _A_1    _A_n  _B 

& + & _i=1 ^n  (-1)^ B (A_i + + A_n)  
^A_n  ^A_1  _ A_1  _A_i-1  
_B _A_i  _A_n  ,
and make use of eq. (), rewritten as
_( A_1  _A_n  _B     I(z,z') _z=z'  =0 .
We thus have
0 &=& ^A_n  ^A_1  _A_1    _A_n  _B  I(z,z') _z=z'  

& + & _i=1 ^n  (-1)^ B (A_i + + A_n)  
^A_n  ^A_1  _ A_1  _A_i-1  
_B _A_i  _A_n   I(z,z') _z=z'  .
The next natural step is to represent
&& (-1)^ B (A_i + + A_n)  
^A_n  ^A_1  _ A_1  _A_i-1  
_B _A_i  _A_n  

=&-&
(-1)^ B (A_i+1  + + A_n)  
^A_n  ^A_1  _ A_1  _A_i-1  
[_A_i  , _B  _A_i+1   _A_n  

&+& (-1)^ B (A_i+1  + + A_n)  
^A_n  ^A_1  _ A_1  _A_i 
_B _A_i+1   _A_n 
and make use of the covariant derivative algebra
(), along with the observation
&(-1)^ B (A_i+1  + + A_n)  
^A_n  ^A_1  _ A_1  _A_i-1  
F_A_i  B  _A_i+1  _A_n 
I(z,z') _z=z'  

& = 
 
.
Repeating this procedure, each  contribution to the second terms in
() can be reduced to the first term
plus additional terms involving graded commutators of covariant derivatives.
Since the torsion  in () is constant,
we then obtain
&&(n+1)  ^A_n  ^A_1  _A_1    _A_n  _B I(z,z')_z=z'  

&=&
_i=1 ^n  i (-1)^ C (A_i+1  + + A_n)  
^A_i  T_A_iB  ^C
^A_n  1 _i 
^A_1 
_ A_1  _C _i 
_A_n   I(z,z') _z=z'  

&& + n i  
^A_n  ^A_1  _ A_1  _A_n-1  
F_A_n B  .
For the first term in the right hand side,
we can again apply  the previous procedure,
and this now simplifies since
T_AB  ^C [_C , _D  =
(-1)^C  T_AB  ^C [_C , _D  =
i  T_AB  ^C F_CD  .
After some algebra, one then arrives at ().




